<TITLE> CA re-commissions frigate Khalid-bin-Walid </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, July 12 (bdnews24.com) -- Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed Thursday re-commissioned BNS frigate Khalid-bin-Walid for Bangladesh Navy. The chief adviser also addressed the officers and sailors of Bangladesh Navy at the commissioning ceremony at the naval jetty in Chittagong. Earlier on his arrival, Fakhruddin was received by naval chief Vice Admiral Sarwar Jahan Nizam. The frigate was built in Daywoo Shipyard in South Korea based on the state of the art technology in 1988. On June 20, 2001 the frigate was commissioned as BNS Bangabandhu for Bangladesh Navy. The frigate was decommissioned on Feb 13, 2002. The frigatecapable of countering any attack in three dimensionswill also be used in extensive surveillance in the exclusive economic zone of the country. The frigate will conduct anti-smuggling, anti-piracy, anti-pollution and rescue operations. bd
